01:23:16,950 --> 01:23:18,826
At her going away party...

1408
01:23:18,911 --> 01:23:22,163
I wanted her to know about that night
we went through the tunnel.

1409
01:23:22,247 --> 01:23:24,165
And how for the first time...

1410
01:23:24,249 --> 01:23:26,292
I felt like I belonged somewhere.

1411
01:23:27,961 --> 01:23:30,630
And tomorrow, she's leaving.

1412
01:23:30,714 --> 01:23:33,424
So I wanted to give her a part of me.

1413
01:23:35,761 --> 01:23:38,221
Are these all your books, Charlie?

1414
01:23:47,606 --> 01:23:49,023
Thanks for staying up with me.

1415
01:23:49,108 --> 01:23:51,734
Sure.

1416
01:23:51,819 --> 01:23:56,781
My brother said Penn State has
this restaurant called Ye Olde College Diner.

1417
01:23:56,865 --> 01:23:59,075
You have to get a grilled
sticky on your first night.

1418
01:23:59,159 --> 01:24:01,494
It's a tradition.

1419
01:24:02,287 --> 01:24:03,621
That sounds like fun.

1420
01:24:03,706 --> 01:24:04,789
Yeah.

1421
01:24:07,459 --> 01:24:10,169
Pretty soon, you'll have
a whole new group offriends, you know.

1422
01:24:11,505 --> 01:24:13,798
You won't even think about this place anymore.

1423
01:24:16,343 --> 01:24:17,677
Yes, I will.

1424
01:24:31,150 --> 01:24:32,817
Had lunch with Craig today.

1425
01:24:34,820 --> 01:24:36,571
Yeah?

1426
01:24:36,655 --> 01:24:39,657
He said he was sorry and that I was right
to break up with him.

1427
01:24:41,910 --> 01:24:46,748
I'm driving away
and was feeling so small.

1428
01:24:46,832 --> 01:24:52,754
Just asking myself,
"Why do I and everyone I love...

1429
01:24:52,838 --> 01:24:55,965
pick people who treat us like we're nothing?"

1430
01:25:00,721 --> 01:25:03,514
We accept the love we think we deserve.

1431
01:25:10,022 --> 01:25:12,356
Then why didn't you ever ask me out?

1432
01:25:19,364 --> 01:25:20,907
I, um—

1433
01:25:20,991 --> 01:25:23,367
I just didn't think that you wanted that.

1434
01:25:24,119 --> 01:25:26,204
Well, what did you want?

1435
01:25:27,539 --> 01:25:29,874
I just want you to be happy.

1436
01:25:30,876 --> 01:25:32,794
Don't you get it, Charlie?

1437
01:25:33,837 --> 01:25:36,380
I can't feel that.

1438
01:25:36,465 --> 01:25:39,634
It's really sweet and everything, but—

1439
01:25:39,718 --> 01:25:42,470
You can'tjust sit there
and put everybody's lives ahead ofyours...

1440
01:25:42,554 --> 01:25:44,222
and think that counts as love.

1441
01:25:44,306 --> 01:25:47,350
I don't want to be somebody's crush.

1442
01:25:47,434 --> 01:25:51,312
I want people to like the real me.

1443
01:25:54,483 --> 01:25:56,859
I know who you are, Sam.

1444
01:26:02,407 --> 01:26:04,242
I know I'm quiet.

1445
01:26:05,494 --> 01:26:08,371
And I know I should speak more.

1446
01:26:08,455 --> 01:26:12,333
But ifyou knew the things
that were in my head most ofthe time...

1447
01:26:12,417 --> 01:26:15,628
you'd know what it really meant.

1448
01:26:17,506 --> 01:26:20,424
How much we're alike...

1449
01:26:20,509 --> 01:26:22,969
and how we've been through the same things.

1450
01:26:24,596 --> 01:26:26,848
And you're not small.

1451
01:26:26,932 --> 01:26:28,266
You're beautiful.

1452
01:26:55,002 --> 01:26:56,127
What's wrong, Charlie?

1453
01:26:56,670 --> 01:26:57,962
Nothing.

1454
01:27:23,989 --> 01:27:26,616
[ Chattering ]

1455
01:27:26,700 --> 01:27:28,159
You know I'm gonna call you all the time.

1456
01:27:28,243 --> 01:27:30,620
- We're gonna see each other in New York.
- All the time.

1457
01:27:33,582 --> 01:27:34,832
Come on, Sam.

1458
01:28:17,209 --> 01:28:18,751
What's wrong, Charlie?

1459
01:28:22,214 --> 01:28:23,673
[ Woman ]
Put your seat belt on.

1460
01:28:23,757 --> 01:28:24,882
We'll meet you there.

1461
01:28:48,615 --> 01:28:50,241
Don't wake your sister.

1462
01:29:03,005 --> 01:29:04,755
It'll be our little secret, okay?

1463
01:29:07,175 --> 01:29:10,636
Look, Charlie, she's fast asleep.

1464
01:29:12,556 --> 01:29:13,639
Don't wake your sister.

1465
01:29:20,981 --> 01:29:25,359
My fault.

1466
01:29:26,028 --> 01:29:27,611
It's all my fault.

1467
01:29:27,696 --> 01:29:29,530
It'll be our little secret. Okay?

1468
01:29:29,614 --> 01:29:30,781
Stop it.

1469
01:29:31,950 --> 01:29:33,117
Stop.

1470
01:29:37,205 --> 01:29:41,333
Stop crying.

1471
01:29:48,383 --> 01:29:49,800
[ Charlie ]
This'll be our little secret.

1472
01:29:53,889 --> 01:29:55,598
[ Phone Ringing ]

1473
01:29:56,558 --> 01:29:58,684
Candace. Your brother's on the phone.

1474
01:30:01,313 --> 01:30:02,563
Hello?

1475
01:30:02,647 --> 01:30:04,899
- Hey, Candace.
- Charlie?

1476
01:30:04,983 --> 01:30:09,570
Sam and Patrick left,
and I can't stop thinking about something.

1477
01:30:09,654 --> 01:30:10,821
Shh. What?

1478
01:30:10,906 --> 01:30:12,156
Candace...

1479
01:30:13,200 --> 01:30:15,785
I killed Aunt Helen, didn't I?

1480
01:30:15,869 --> 01:30:17,620
She died getting my birthday present...

1481
01:30:17,704 --> 01:30:20,748
so I guess I killed her, right?

1482
01:30:20,832 --> 01:30:22,917
I've tried to stop thinking that,
but I can't.

1483
01:30:23,001 --> 01:30:24,668
She keeps driving away and dying.

1484
01:30:24,753 --> 01:30:26,295
Call the police and send them to my house.

1485
01:30:26,379 --> 01:30:28,130
I can't stop her. I'm crazy again.

1486
01:30:28,215 --> 01:30:29,799
No. Charlie, listen to me.

1487
01:30:29,883 --> 01:30:31,926
Mom and Dad are gonna be home
with Chris any second.

1488
01:30:32,010 --> 01:30:34,303
I'mjust thinking...

1489
01:30:34,387 --> 01:30:36,597
what if I wanted her to die, Candace?

1490
01:30:36,681 --> 01:30:38,849
- What? Charlie?
- [ Line Clicks ]

1491
01:30:38,934 --> 01:30:40,059
Charlie!

1492
01:31:15,137 --> 01:31:16,428
Charlie?

1493
01:31:17,514 --> 01:31:19,056
I'm Dr. Burton.

1494
01:31:23,770 --> 01:31:25,271
Where am I?

1495
01:31:25,355 --> 01:31:27,523
Mayview Hospital.

1496
01:31:29,484 --> 01:31:34,071
You, uh—
You have to let me go. My dad can't afford it.

1497
01:31:34,156 --> 01:31:36,157
Oh, don't worry about that.

1498
01:31:36,241 --> 01:31:41,162
No. I saw them when I was little...

1499
01:31:41,246 --> 01:31:43,497
and I don't want to be a Mayview kid.

1500
01:31:43,582 --> 01:31:45,374
Just tell me how to stop it.

1501
01:31:45,458 --> 01:31:46,792
Stop what?

1502
01:31:47,586 --> 01:31:49,461
Seeing it.

1503
01:31:52,007 --> 01:31:56,093
All their lives all the time.

1504
01:31:57,137 --> 01:31:59,096
How do you stop seeing it?

1505
01:31:59,181 --> 01:32:01,056
Seeing what, Charlie?

1506
01:32:01,141 --> 01:32:06,729
There is so much pain.

1507
01:32:06,813 --> 01:32:11,442
And I don't know how to not notice it.

1508
01:32:11,526 --> 01:32:13,360
What's hurting you?

1509
01:32:13,445 --> 01:32:14,737
No, not me.

1510
01:32:14,821 --> 01:32:19,366
It's them. It's everyone. It never stops.

1511
01:32:20,493 --> 01:32:21,660
Do you understand?

1512
01:32:28,627 --> 01:32:30,669
What about yourAunt Helen?

1513
01:32:34,633 --> 01:32:36,967
What about her?

1514
01:32:37,052 --> 01:32:38,594
Do you see her?

1515
01:32:41,848 --> 01:32:43,974
Yes.

1516
01:32:44,059 --> 01:32:46,060
She had a terrible life.

1517
01:32:48,980 --> 01:32:50,064
God, what am I supposed to—

1518
01:32:50,148 --> 01:32:53,317
You said some things about her in your sleep.

1519
01:32:53,401 --> 01:32:55,236
I don't care.

1520
01:32:55,320 --> 01:32:56,820
Ifyou want to get better...

1521
01:32:57,989 --> 01:32:59,657
you have to.

1522
01:33:06,414 --> 01:33:07,414
She—

1523
01:33:08,917 --> 01:33:11,335
She was insane.

1524
01:33:12,170 --> 01:33:13,545
I'm just sayin'.

1525
01:33:14,547 --> 01:33:15,839
She—

1526
01:33:17,342 --> 01:33:18,759
Charlie?

1527
01:33:18,843 --> 01:33:21,178
You gonna let me help you here?

1528
01:33:24,224 --> 01:33:25,432
Okay.

1529
01:33:26,726 --> 01:33:29,520
Do you remember anything
before you blacked out?

1530
01:33:32,190 --> 01:33:34,984
I remember leaving Sam's house.

1531
01:33:35,777 --> 01:33:38,862
I was walking home. And—

1532
01:33:40,448 --> 01:33:42,616
[ Charlie ]
I was in the hospital for a while.

1533
01:33:44,411 --> 01:33:47,663
I won't go into detail about all of it.

1534
01:33:47,747 --> 01:33:51,959
But I will say there were some very bad days.

1535
01:33:52,043 --> 01:33:54,712
And some unexpected beautiful days.

1536
01:33:57,716 --> 01:34:01,385
The worst day was the time my doctor
told my mom and dad...

1537
01:34:01,469 --> 01:34:03,387
what Aunt Helen did to me.

1538
01:34:10,228 --> 01:34:11,270
Honey?

1539
01:34:14,065 --> 01:34:15,733
I'm so sorry.

1540
01:34:29,914 --> 01:34:32,833
The best days were those
when I could have visitors.

1541
01:34:32,917 --> 01:34:35,377
My brother and sister always came for those...

1542
01:34:35,462 --> 01:34:38,547
until Chris had to go to training camp.

1543
01:34:38,631 --> 01:34:40,758
He's going to be first string this year.

1544
01:34:42,886 --> 01:34:46,805
My sister told me she met a nice guy
at her summerjob.

1545
01:34:50,810 --> 01:34:53,270
Here he is.

1546
01:34:53,355 --> 01:34:57,191
So I'll see you Thursday at 6:00, right?

1547
01:34:57,275 --> 01:34:59,276
- Okay.
